        <h1 class="heading-large">Roadmap</h1>
            <p>Here&rsquo;s a list of the new functionality we&rsquo;re planning to offer through GOV.UK Pay over the next 6 to 9 months.</p>

            <p class="panel panel-border-wide">This roadmap is a only a guide and may change from month to month.</p>

            <h2 class="heading-small">June 2017</h2>
                <ul class="list list-bullet">
                    <li>Self service account creation and team management</li>
                    <li>Support for Barclays online card payments (ePDQ)</li>
                    <li>Disaster recovery within 1 hour with an additional Amazon Web Services region</li>
                </ul>
            <h2 class="heading-small">July to September 2017</h2>
                <ul class="list list-bullet">
                    <li>Improved refund-related reporting</li>
                    <li>Reporting for settlement of funds to merchant (business) bank account</li>
                    <li>Basic aggregate reporting dashboards for payments</li>
                    <li>Support for Maestro and Visa Electron</li>
                </ul>
            <h2 class="heading-small">September 2017 onwards</h2>
                <ul class="list list-bullet">
                    <li>Include payment statuses</li>
                    <li>Foreign currency support</li>
                    <li>Foreign language support</li>
                    <li>Delayed capture (more efficient security process)</li>
                    <li>Refund confirmation emails</li>
                    <li>Recurring card payments</li>
                </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-medium">Queries and suggestions</h2>
            <p>If you want to find out more about these features, or have some needs that GOV.UK Pay isn&rsquo;t yet meeting, please get in touch with us by emailing <a href="mailto:govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk">govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk</a> or chat with us in our <a href="">cross-government Slack channel</a>.</p>
